{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4aaa7611-0e04-4301-9689-5189277d75b8","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. Here are your main options:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the current thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` then `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n**Using LLDB with SOS** (Linux):\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core <your-file.dmp>\n```\n\n**Using WinDbg** (Windows):\nLoad the dump, then use `!analyze -v` and SOS commands like `!clrstack`, `!pe`.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file? If so, provide the path to the `.dmp` file and I can walk through the investigation interactively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b0c85825-d468-49b8-ad89-4d0b9a180cb0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nI'll provide guidance on analyzing the dump file directly.","outputTokens":370,"requestId":"CB00:392B11:745C71:8557EF:6A052B22"},"id":"e18e7dc7-88b1-4ca1-afd9-dd16e1be19a9","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:53:48.948Z","parentId":"d9ce9d28-777a-40e5-b2ec-0d30df1be2ea"}
